=Description=

"Ecology In The 20th Century is an intellectual and political history of the ecology movement from its beginnings in the late nineteenth century to the present.This book provides the first thorough study of the origins and background of 'Green' politics which has in recent years carved out a significant political constituency throughout Europe and America."

